    "lettering": "Letters are extremely thin, and curved. The first vertical stem of the eta in line 2 appears to join the vertical stem of the kappa in line 1, thus making it difficult to be precise about letter heights in lines 1-2. The orthography is extremely strange, particularly in the tail of the tau in line 3 which gives the impression of the letter 'J'.",
